The paper discusses the use of Evolution Strategies, a type of reinforcement learning method, for solving multi-agent problems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and robotics, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on multi-agent problems, which could also place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-categories.
